description: I am selling my 1985 Sun Runner Cuddy. All FIBERGLASS This boat has the Mercruiser 470 170hp 4cyl. It runs extremely well, and I have recently changed the fluids. It seems to be great on fuel. The boat has a new Autocraft battery from Advance, with I think a 3 year warranty. The interior is in what I think to be really good shape for a 1985, the only tear in the vinyl is on the rear flat seat over the engine. The front seats have new boxes under them. I have also installed a "cigarette lighter" charging port on the dash for phones and other things. The trailer is a Calkins brand, with new wiring and lights. It pulls extremely well in the hills between Nashville and Lake Monroe. My wife and I purchased this boat in the spring, but after only going out on it a handful of times, realized a boat is not for us. The boat and the trailer both have clean and clear titles, in my name. The price is somewhat negotiable, however, I will only take the boat for a test drive at full asking price. I'm not interested in trades unless its a Spitfire or similar.
title: 1985 Sun Runner 22' Cuddy - LOWER PRICE!

description: 1997 Donzi 3250 LXC Fast and Fun Sport Cruiser!  Max Speed 52 MPH!  Cruising Speed: 30-32 MPH Lenght Overall:  33'7" Beam:  10' 4" Draft:  3' 1" Gross Tons:  13 GRT Engine #1:  Mercruiser, 330HP, 7.4 Liter, with 375 HRS. Engine #2:  Mercruiser, 330HP, 7.4 Liter, with 392 HRS. Both Engines have Bravo III Outdrives (Duo Props are Stainless) Fuel Capacity:  Twin 100-gallon tanks Batteries:  Three inline for boat; one for house. Generator:  Kohler 4kW (gas) Electronics:  VHF, AM/FM/CD/Sirius Satellite, TV w/ VCR, Full/Twin Instruments Cabin Layout:  Forward is equipped with a double-berth, large closet, VHS Player.  Dining area is starboard amidships fitted with a large U-shaped dinette that converts to bed.  Aft is a full-size bed.  Head is port with hand held shower, single Stainless Steel sink, and vacuflush head.  Galley has Norcold refrigerator, Kenyon electric or alcohol range with 2 burners, Tappan microwave, wood cabinets with Formica type counter coverings, custom window treatments, and carpet flooring (removable carpet). Above deck:  Remote spotlight, Horizon 500 windlass, wet bar with U-Line ice maker, single compartment sink, hot & cold shower, swim platform with fold-down ladder. Instruments:  Custom Dana Controls, dual: RPM, temp, volt, oil, fuel, mph & trim gauges.  Remote spotlight and remote windless controls. The trailer that comes with the boat is a 2005 Loadmaster Trailer that was custom-made for the boat one week after the boat was purchased.  The trailer was used to bring the boat from Knoxville, Tennessee (where purchased) to my home and has been used once in the Spring and once in the Fall each year after purchase.  I keep the boat on Lake Monroe here in Bloomington so the trailer hardly has any miles on it.  The following is a description that was emailed to me when I decided to buy the trailer.  It has the optional tool box on front, LED lights, and Sling Pockets.  (Marinas can lift boat off trailer). Three (3) 6,000lbs. Safe-T-Lube, Drop-Center, Submersible Axles 16,002lbs GVWR  Net Carry Capacity 13,582lbs. Mig-Welded Channel Steel Construction All-Wheel Electric Brakes 8-Ply Radial Tires Morton Silver, Clear-Coated Wheels Adjustable Treated Lumber, Edges Routed, Marine-Carpeted Bunks Structural Fenders with Anti-Skid 7,000lbs. Drop-leg Tongue Jack Manual 2 Speed Winch with 6,000lbs., Strap 20,000lbs. Locking Coupler (2 5/16 Ball) Two Safety Cables. Break-away System with Built-in Battery Charger Epoxy Primer, Polyurethane Paint, Sealed with Clearcoat. Painted Pinstripes. Sealed, Submersible Lights. All Electrical Connections Shrinkwrapped. $5,525.00 plus Delivery or Sales Tax if Applicable March, 2005 Sling Pockets = +$100, All LED Lights = +$50 Please contact me if you would like pictures emailed to you. SERIOUS INQUIRIES ONLY!  IF YOU MAKE AN APPOINTMENT TO VIEW PLEASE HAVE THE COURTESY TO SHOW UP! Boat has been stored in enclosed pole building over winter since purchased.
